and actively simulate thousands of potential future market trajectories for each possible action,
selecting the policy that maximizes expected utility over a distribution of simulated futures.
Crucially, our framework introduces a novel state component—the Reflexivity Vector—to
quantify and navigate the market’s self-referential feedback loops, a concept central to Soros’s
