The **Reflexivity Vector (Rt)** quantifies the market’s self-awareness and the potential
for feedback loops. Its components include:
• Strategy Discourse Metric: Measures the volume and velocity of discussion around
specific trading strategies (e.g., ”gamma squeeze,” ”risk parity”) on social media and in
financial news.
• Crowdedness Indicator: Uses institutional holdings data and options market position-
ing to estimate the concentration of capital in specific trades.
• Model Correlation: A metric that estimates the correlation of our own model’s sig-
nals with those of widely-used quantitative strategies (e.g., trend-following, momentum).
High correlation signals a crowded trade and increased reflexive risk.
