4 Axiomatic System and Formal Proof
The axiomatic system is updated with a fifth axiom.
Axiom 1 (Reflexivity). The market is a reflexive system. The state transition function P(St+1|St,At)
is dependent not only on the state St, but also on the distribution of predictive models and be-
liefs held by market participants, a quantity partially captured by the Reflexivity Vector Rt.
The formal proof of policy existence follows, now grounded in the framework of model-
based RL and planning, which has its own robust theoretical guarantees.
