5 Discussion and Conclusion
This paper argued for and demonstrated a new paradigm for algorithmic trading. By replacing
reactive policies with a learned Generative World Model and an active planning process, we
create agents with a rudimentary form of foresight. By explicitly modeling market reflexivity,
we equip these agents to navigate the self-referential nature of financial markets.
The success of our Generative Agent in an adversarial backtesting environment provides
strong evidence that this approach yields more robust and resilient strategies. Future work
will focus on scaling the simulation capacity of the agent and exploring more sophisticated
hierarchical planning algorithms. This research marks a step away from models that merely
play the market, and towards models that can genuinely reason about it.
